This document provides the code to replicate the experiments from the paper

A general framework for implementing distances for categorical variables

by Michel van de Velden, Alfonso Iodice DâEnza, Angelos Markos and Carlo Cavicchia

Data structures

The considered distances are described in Table 1 of the paper

distance description
SM simple matching
IOF Iof
OF of
Goodall 3 Goodall 3
Goodall 4 Goodall 4
chi-2 chi-square distance
VE variable entropy
VM variable mutability
KL Kullback-Leibler
TVD total variation distance
Supervised TVD one-vs-all variation of TVD
Supervised TVD full all-vs-all variation of TVD

Synthetic data set

We refer to a \(n=1000\) by \(Q=10\) categorical dataset.

A different dataset is considered for each scenario;

  • balanced/unbalanced: the classes of the response are of equal size or not

  • structure: mild/strong is the discriminant power of the active variables

Of the \(Q=10\) attribute considered, 6 are noise.

The synthetic data sets are generated as described in the paper Cluster Correspondence Analysis.

Real data

Supervised learning: KNN-based experiment

Analysis and results on synthetic data sets

For each scenario and considered distance, a KNN classifier for a grid of values \(K=\{5,10,15,20\}\) is trained

Code 
k_vec = c(1,5,15,30,50)

selected_distances = c("tot_var_dist", "gifi_chi2",
         "supervised","supervised_full", "matching","eskin",
         "goodall_3","goodall_4","iof","of","lin",
         "var_entropy","var_mutability","kullback-leibler")



cat_data_structure = tibble(structure=rep(c("mild","strong"), times=2),
                            balance = rep(c("unbalanced","balanced"), each=2),
                            cat_data = list(cat_data_a, cat_data_b,cat_data_c,cat_data_d),
                            true_clusters=list(true_clusters_a,true_clusters_b,
                                               true_clusters_c,true_clusters_d)) |> 
  mutate(cat_data = map2(.x=cat_data,.y=true_clusters, ~.x |>
                           select(a:d,i:p) |> 
                           mutate(response=.y)),
         distance_method = map(1:4,~selected_distances)
  )

The hyper-parameter tuning process is done via 5-fold cross-validation, the process is repeated 10 times

Code 
cat_data_resamples = cat_data_structure |> 
  mutate(
    cv_iterations = map(1:n(), ~ 1:10)
         ) |> unnest(cv_iterations) |> 
   mutate(
    cross_validation = map(.x=cat_data,~vfold_cv(.x, v= 5, strata=response)),
    fold_id = map(.x=cross_validation,~.x$id),
    fold_splits = map(.x=cross_validation,~.x$splits),
    k_par = map(1:n(),~k_vec)
   ) |>  unnest(cols = distance_method) |>  unnest(cols = k_par) |> 
  unnest(cols = c(fold_id,fold_splits)) |> 
  dplyr::select(-cross_validation)

The results are produced, and the accuracies computed for each combination of folds, and iterations

Code 
cat_data_knn_results = cat_data_resamples |> 
  mutate(knn_results = pmap(.l = list(fold_splits, k_par,distance_method),
                            .f = ~cat_nearest_neighbors(train_df = analysis(..1),
                                                        assess_df = assessment(..1),
                                                        k=..2, method=..3),
                            ),
  predictions = map(.x = knn_results,~.x$.pred),
  truth = map(.x = knn_results,~.x$truth),
  same_levs = map2_dbl(.x = predictions,.y=truth,
                       ~(length(levels(.x))==length(levels(.y)))),
  predictions = map2(.x = predictions,.y = truth,
                     ~factor(.x, levels = levels(.y))),
  knn_accuracy=map2_dbl(.x = predictions,.y = truth,
                        ~accuracy_vec(truth = .y,estimate = .x))
  )

Then, for each scenario and distance measure, the accuracies are averaged over the CV folds first, and then over the iterations

Code 
cat_knn_PM_scenarios_accuracies = cat_data_knn_results |> 
    group_by(structure, balance ,distance_method,k_par,cv_iterations) |>
  summarise(cv_accuracy=mean(knn_accuracy),.groups="rowwise") |> ungroup()|>
  group_by(structure, balance ,distance_method,k_par) |> 
  summarise(sd_cv_accuracy=sd(cv_accuracy),
            cv_accuracy=mean(cv_accuracy),.groups="rowwise") |>
  ungroup() |> group_by(structure, balance,distance_method)

Finally, the tuned classifier accuracy is computed

Select the best K for each distance method and data set

Code 
cat_knn_PM_scenarios_accuracies_tuned = cat_knn_PM_scenarios_accuracies |>
  slice_max(cv_accuracy,with_ties = FALSE)|>
  mutate(
    distance_method = str_to_title(distance_method)
  )

And the results are desplayed in the plot

  mutate(scenario=paste0(structure,"_",balance),
         distance_method = distance_method |> fct_recode("SM"="Matching",
                                                     "IOF"="Iof",

                                                     "Supervised TVD full"="Supervised_full"
                                                     ) |> as.character(),

                                       within = scenario, sep = ":")
         ) |>

  )  + 
  scale_y_discrete(label=labelize)+
  scale_size(range=c(.5,2.5))+guides(size="none")+

  xlab("accuracy") + ylab("distances")+
  scale_color_discrete(breaks=c("SM","Eskin","Lin","IOF","OF","Goodall 3","Goodall 4","VE","VM","TVD","chi2","KL","Supervised TVD","Supervised TVD full"))#+scale_size(range=c(.5,2.5))

Analysis and results on real data sets

Code 
dataset_names = c("vote","australian","wbcd", "tictac","balance","tae",
                        "lympho","soybeanlarge","cars")

benchmark_data = tibble(datasets=dataset_names) |>
  mutate(prepped_data = map(.x=datasets,~select_data(.x)),
         prepped_data = map(.x=prepped_data, ~cbind(.x$df,response=.x$y)),
                  distance_method = rerun(selected_distances,.n=n())
  )

For each dataset and distance considered, we do a KNN, tuning the parameter on the grid 1, 3, 7, 13, 21 via 5-fold cross-validation. We repeat the process 10 times.

Code 
benchmark_data_resamples = benchmark_data |> 
  mutate(
    cv_iterations = map(1:n(), ~ 1:10)
    # cv_iterations = rerun(1:2, .n = n())
  ) |> unnest(cv_iterations) |> 
  mutate(
    cross_validation = map(.x=prepped_data,~vfold_cv(.x, v= 5, strata=response)),
    fold_id = map(.x=cross_validation,~.x$id),
    fold_splits = map(.x=cross_validation,~.x$splits),
    k_par = rerun(c(1,3,7,13,21),.n=n()),
    # k_par = rerun(c(1,3),.n=n()),
  ) |> unnest(cols = distance_method)|> unnest(cols = k_par) |> unnest(cols = c(fold_id,fold_splits)) |> 
  dplyr::select(-cross_validation)

Apply the KNN on all fold/distance/dataset combinations

benchmark_results_training = benchmark_data_resamples |>

accuracy_results_knn = benchmark_results_training |>
  mutate(

    predictions = map(.x=knn_results,~.x$.pred),
    truth = map(.x=knn_results,~.x$truth),
    same_levs = map2_dbl(.x = predictions,.y=truth,~(length(levels(.x))==length(levels(.y)))),
    predictions = map2(.x=predictions,.y=truth,~factor(.x,levels=levels(.y))),
    knn_accuracy=map2_dbl(.x=predictions,.y=truth,~accuracy_vec(truth=.y,estimate=.x))
  ) |> group_by(datasets,distance_method,k_par,cv_iterations) |>
  summarise(cv_accuracy=mean(knn_accuracy)) |> ungroup() |>
  group_by(datasets,distance_method,k_par) |> 
  summarise(sd_cv_accuracy=sd(cv_accuracy),
            cv_accuracy=mean(cv_accuracy)
  ) |> ungroup() |>
  group_by(datasets,distance_method)

Unsupervised learning: partitioning around medoid-based experiment

Analysis and results on synthetic data sets

Code 
pam_synth_results_list=list()
set.seed(123)
for(cv_iter in 1:10){

  cat_data_resamples_pam = cat_data_structure |> 
  mutate(
         cross_validation = map(.x=cat_data,~vfold_cv(.x, v= 5, strata=response)),
         fold_id = map(.x=cross_validation,~.x$id),
         fold_splits = map(.x=cross_validation,~.x$splits),
         n_clusters  = 4
  )|> unnest(cols = distance_method) |> unnest(cols = c(fold_id,fold_splits)) |> #|> unnest(cols = k_par)
  dplyr::select(-cross_validation,-cat_data) |>
  mutate(train_fold=map(.x=fold_splits,.f=~analysis(.x)),
         test_fold=map(.x=fold_splits,.f=~assessment(.x))
  ) |> 
  dplyr::select(-fold_splits)   |>
    mutate(
         distance_res = pmap(.l=list(..1 = train_fold,..2 = distance_method),#,..3 = 1
                        .f=~cdist(x = ..1 |> select(-response),
                                  y = ..1 |> pull(response),
                                  method = ..2)),
         distance_mat = map(.x=distance_res,.f=function(x=.x){x$distance_mat;
         return(x$distance_mat)}),
         delta = map(.x=distance_res,~.x$delta),
         delta_names = map(.x=distance_res,~.x$delta_names)
         )

  cat_data_results_pam = cat_data_resamples_pam |> 
    mutate(
      pam_solution = map2(.x=distance_mat,.y=n_clusters,.f=~pam(x = .x,k = .y)),
      pam_clust = map(.x=pam_solution, .f= ~return(.x$clustering |> factor())),
      pam_medoid_ids = map(.x=pam_solution, ~return(.x$id.med)),
      true_clust_test = map(.x = test_fold, ~return(.x |> pull(response))),
      test_data = map(.x = test_fold, ~return(.x |> select(-response))),
      train_data = map(.x = train_fold, ~return(.x |> select(-response))),
      medoids = map2(.x = train_data,.y=pam_medoid_ids, ~return(.x[.y,])),
      clust_test = pmap(.l=list(..1 = medoids,..2 = test_data,..3=delta, ..4 = delta_names),
                        ~predict_pam(medoids = ..1, newdata=..2, delta=..3, delta_names = ..4)),
      measure =  map2_dbl(.x = true_clust_test,.y = clust_test,
                          .f=function(x=.x,y=.y) clustComp(c1 = x, c2 = y)$ARI
      )
    )
  

   
pam_synth_results_list[[cv_iter]] = cat_data_results_pam |> dplyr::select(structure,balance,distance_method,measure,fold_id) |>
  group_by(structure,balance,distance_method) |> 
  summarise(ARI=mean(measure)) |> ungroup() |> mutate(cv_iteration=cv_iter)
}

pam_results_list=list()
set.seed(123)
for(cv_iter in 1:10){
  print(cv_iter)
  benchmark_data_resamples_pam = benchmark_data |> 
  mutate(
         cross_validation = map(.x=prepped_data,~vfold_cv(.x, v= 5, strata=response)),
         fold_id = map(.x=cross_validation,~.x$id),
         fold_splits = map(.x=cross_validation,~.x$splits),
         n_clusters  = map_dbl(.x=prepped_data,~length(levels(.x$response)))
  )|> unnest(cols = distance_method) |> unnest(cols = c(fold_id,fold_splits)) |> #|> unnest(cols = k_par)
  dplyr::select(-cross_validation,-prepped_data) |>
  mutate(train_fold=map(.x=fold_splits,.f=~analysis(.x)),
         test_fold=map(.x=fold_splits,.f=~assessment(.x))
  ) |> 
  dplyr::select(-fold_splits)|>
    
    mutate(
         distance_res = pmap(.l=list(..1 = train_fold,..2 = distance_method),
                        .f=~cdist(x = ..1 |> dplyr::select(-response),
                                  y = ..1 |> pull(response),
                                  method = ..2)),
             distance_mat = map(.x=distance_res,.f=function(x=.x){x$distance_mat;
         return(x$distance_mat)}),
         delta = map(.x=distance_res,~.x$delta),
         delta_names = map(.x=distance_res,~.x$delta_names)
         )

benchmark_results_pam = benchmark_data_resamples_pam |> 
  mutate(
      pam_solution = map2(.x=distance_mat,.y=n_clusters,.f=~pam(x = .x,k = .y))
  )
   
   benchmark_results_pam = benchmark_results_pam |> 
  mutate(
      pam_clust = map(.x=pam_solution, .f= ~return(.x$clustering |> factor())),
      pam_medoid_ids = map(.x=pam_solution, ~return(.x$id.med)),
      true_clust_test = map(.x = test_fold, ~return(.x |> pull(response))),
      test_data = map(.x = test_fold, ~return(.x |> select(-response))),
      train_data = map(.x = train_fold, ~return(.x |> select(-response))),
      medoids = map2(.x = train_data,.y=pam_medoid_ids, ~return(.x[.y,]))
      )
   
   benchmark_results_pam = benchmark_results_pam |> 
  mutate(
      clust_test = pmap(.l=list(..1 = medoids,..2 = test_data,..3=delta, ..4 = delta_names),
                        ~predict_pam(medoids = ..1, newdata=..2, delta=..3, delta_names = ..4)),
      measure =  map2_dbl(.x = true_clust_test,.y = clust_test,
                     .f=function(x=.x,y=.y) clustComp(c1 = x, c2 = y)$ARI
    )
  )
   
pam_results_list[[cv_iter]] = benchmark_results_pam |> dplyr::select(datasets,distance_method,measure,fold_id) |> group_by(datasets,distance_method) |> 
  summarise(ARI=mean(measure)) |> ungroup() |> mutate(cv_iteration=cv_iter)
}

## Synthetic data set

We refer to a $n=1000$ by $Q=10$ categorical dataset. 

A different dataset is considered for each scenario; 

- balanced/unbalanced: the classes of the response are of equal size or not

- structure: mild/strong is the discriminant power of the active variables

Of the $Q=10$ attribute considered, 6 are noise.

The synthetic data sets are generated as described in the paper [Cluster Correspondence Analysis](https://rdcu.be/dpOeu).

# Supervised learning: KNN-based experiment



## Analysis and results on synthetic data sets

For each scenario and considered distance, a KNN classifier for a grid of values $K=\{5,10,15,20\}$ is trained

```{r,eval=FALSE}
k_vec = c(1,5,15,30,50)

selected_distances = c("tot_var_dist", "gifi_chi2",
         "supervised","supervised_full", "matching","eskin",
         "goodall_3","goodall_4","iof","of","lin",
         "var_entropy","var_mutability","kullback-leibler")



cat_data_structure = tibble(structure=rep(c("mild","strong"), times=2),
                            balance = rep(c("unbalanced","balanced"), each=2),
                            cat_data = list(cat_data_a, cat_data_b,cat_data_c,cat_data_d),
                            true_clusters=list(true_clusters_a,true_clusters_b,
                                               true_clusters_c,true_clusters_d)) |> 
  mutate(cat_data = map2(.x=cat_data,.y=true_clusters, ~.x |>
                           select(a:d,i:p) |> 
                           mutate(response=.y)),
         distance_method = map(1:4,~selected_distances)
  )
```

The hyper-parameter tuning process is done via 5-fold cross-validation, the process is repeated 10 times

```{r, eval=FALSE}
cat_data_resamples = cat_data_structure |> 
  mutate(
    cv_iterations = map(1:n(), ~ 1:10)
         ) |> unnest(cv_iterations) |> 
   mutate(
    cross_validation = map(.x=cat_data,~vfold_cv(.x, v= 5, strata=response)),
    fold_id = map(.x=cross_validation,~.x$id),
    fold_splits = map(.x=cross_validation,~.x$splits),
    k_par = map(1:n(),~k_vec)
   ) |>  unnest(cols = distance_method) |>  unnest(cols = k_par) |> 
  unnest(cols = c(fold_id,fold_splits)) |> 
  dplyr::select(-cross_validation)
```  

The results are produced, and the accuracies computed for each combination of folds, and iterations

```{r,eval=FALSE}
cat_data_knn_results = cat_data_resamples |> 
  mutate(knn_results = pmap(.l = list(fold_splits, k_par,distance_method),
                            .f = ~cat_nearest_neighbors(train_df = analysis(..1),
                                                        assess_df = assessment(..1),
                                                        k=..2, method=..3),
                            ),
  predictions = map(.x = knn_results,~.x$.pred),
  truth = map(.x = knn_results,~.x$truth),
  same_levs = map2_dbl(.x = predictions,.y=truth,
                       ~(length(levels(.x))==length(levels(.y)))),
  predictions = map2(.x = predictions,.y = truth,
                     ~factor(.x, levels = levels(.y))),
  knn_accuracy=map2_dbl(.x = predictions,.y = truth,
                        ~accuracy_vec(truth = .y,estimate = .x))
  )
```

Then, for each scenario and distance measure, the accuracies are averaged over the CV folds first, and then over the iterations 

```{r,eval=FALSE, warning = FALSE}
cat_knn_PM_scenarios_accuracies = cat_data_knn_results |> 
    group_by(structure, balance ,distance_method,k_par,cv_iterations) |>
  summarise(cv_accuracy=mean(knn_accuracy),.groups="rowwise") |> ungroup()|>
  group_by(structure, balance ,distance_method,k_par) |> 
  summarise(sd_cv_accuracy=sd(cv_accuracy),
            cv_accuracy=mean(cv_accuracy),.groups="rowwise") |>
  ungroup() |> group_by(structure, balance,distance_method)
```

Finally, the tuned classifier accuracy is computed

```{r echo=FALSE,eval=FALSE}
save(file="PM_synthetic_cat_four_scenario_knn_experiment_pattern_recognition.RData",cat_knn_PM_scenarios_accuracies)
```

# Unsupervised learning: partitioning around medoid-based experiment

## Analysis and results on synthetic data sets

```{r, eval=FALSE}

pam_synth_results_list=list()
set.seed(123)
for(cv_iter in 1:10){

  cat_data_resamples_pam = cat_data_structure |> 
  mutate(
         cross_validation = map(.x=cat_data,~vfold_cv(.x, v= 5, strata=response)),
         fold_id = map(.x=cross_validation,~.x$id),
         fold_splits = map(.x=cross_validation,~.x$splits),
         n_clusters  = 4
  )|> unnest(cols = distance_method) |> unnest(cols = c(fold_id,fold_splits)) |> #|> unnest(cols = k_par)
  dplyr::select(-cross_validation,-cat_data) |>
  mutate(train_fold=map(.x=fold_splits,.f=~analysis(.x)),
         test_fold=map(.x=fold_splits,.f=~assessment(.x))
  ) |> 
  dplyr::select(-fold_splits)   |>
    mutate(
         distance_res = pmap(.l=list(..1 = train_fold,..2 = distance_method),#,..3 = 1
                        .f=~cdist(x = ..1 |> select(-response),
                                  y = ..1 |> pull(response),
                                  method = ..2)),
         distance_mat = map(.x=distance_res,.f=function(x=.x){x$distance_mat;
         return(x$distance_mat)}),
         delta = map(.x=distance_res,~.x$delta),
         delta_names = map(.x=distance_res,~.x$delta_names)
         )

  cat_data_results_pam = cat_data_resamples_pam |> 
    mutate(
      pam_solution = map2(.x=distance_mat,.y=n_clusters,.f=~pam(x = .x,k = .y)),
      pam_clust = map(.x=pam_solution, .f= ~return(.x$clustering |> factor())),
      pam_medoid_ids = map(.x=pam_solution, ~return(.x$id.med)),
      true_clust_test = map(.x = test_fold, ~return(.x |> pull(response))),
      test_data = map(.x = test_fold, ~return(.x |> select(-response))),
      train_data = map(.x = train_fold, ~return(.x |> select(-response))),
      medoids = map2(.x = train_data,.y=pam_medoid_ids, ~return(.x[.y,])),
      clust_test = pmap(.l=list(..1 = medoids,..2 = test_data,..3=delta, ..4 = delta_names),
                        ~predict_pam(medoids = ..1, newdata=..2, delta=..3, delta_names = ..4)),
      measure =  map2_dbl(.x = true_clust_test,.y = clust_test,
                          .f=function(x=.x,y=.y) clustComp(c1 = x, c2 = y)$ARI
      )
    )
  

   
pam_synth_results_list[[cv_iter]] = cat_data_results_pam |> dplyr::select(structure,balance,distance_method,measure,fold_id) |>
  group_by(structure,balance,distance_method) |> 
  summarise(ARI=mean(measure)) |> ungroup() |> mutate(cv_iteration=cv_iter)
}
```

```{r,eval=FALSE}

pam_results_list=list()
set.seed(123)
for(cv_iter in 1:10){
  print(cv_iter)
  benchmark_data_resamples_pam = benchmark_data |> 
  mutate(
         cross_validation = map(.x=prepped_data,~vfold_cv(.x, v= 5, strata=response)),
         fold_id = map(.x=cross_validation,~.x$id),
         fold_splits = map(.x=cross_validation,~.x$splits),
         n_clusters  = map_dbl(.x=prepped_data,~length(levels(.x$response)))
  )|> unnest(cols = distance_method) |> unnest(cols = c(fold_id,fold_splits)) |> #|> unnest(cols = k_par)
  dplyr::select(-cross_validation,-prepped_data) |>
  mutate(train_fold=map(.x=fold_splits,.f=~analysis(.x)),
         test_fold=map(.x=fold_splits,.f=~assessment(.x))
  ) |> 
  dplyr::select(-fold_splits)|>
    
    mutate(
         distance_res = pmap(.l=list(..1 = train_fold,..2 = distance_method),
                        .f=~cdist(x = ..1 |> dplyr::select(-response),
                                  y = ..1 |> pull(response),
                                  method = ..2)),
             distance_mat = map(.x=distance_res,.f=function(x=.x){x$distance_mat;
         return(x$distance_mat)}),
         delta = map(.x=distance_res,~.x$delta),
         delta_names = map(.x=distance_res,~.x$delta_names)
         )

benchmark_results_pam = benchmark_data_resamples_pam |> 
  mutate(
      pam_solution = map2(.x=distance_mat,.y=n_clusters,.f=~pam(x = .x,k = .y))
  )
   
   benchmark_results_pam = benchmark_results_pam |> 
  mutate(
      pam_clust = map(.x=pam_solution, .f= ~return(.x$clustering |> factor())),
      pam_medoid_ids = map(.x=pam_solution, ~return(.x$id.med)),
      true_clust_test = map(.x = test_fold, ~return(.x |> pull(response))),
      test_data = map(.x = test_fold, ~return(.x |> select(-response))),
      train_data = map(.x = train_fold, ~return(.x |> select(-response))),
      medoids = map2(.x = train_data,.y=pam_medoid_ids, ~return(.x[.y,]))
      )
   
   benchmark_results_pam = benchmark_results_pam |> 
  mutate(
      clust_test = pmap(.l=list(..1 = medoids,..2 = test_data,..3=delta, ..4 = delta_names),
                        ~predict_pam(medoids = ..1, newdata=..2, delta=..3, delta_names = ..4)),
      measure =  map2_dbl(.x = true_clust_test,.y = clust_test,
                     .f=function(x=.x,y=.y) clustComp(c1 = x, c2 = y)$ARI
    )
  )
   
pam_results_list[[cv_iter]] = benchmark_results_pam |> dplyr::select(datasets,distance_method,measure,fold_id) |> group_by(datasets,distance_method) |> 
  summarise(ARI=mean(measure)) |> ungroup() |> mutate(cv_iteration=cv_iter)
}
```
